      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 59 六四</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 59 六四</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六四：渙其群，元吉。渙有丘，匪夷所思。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fourth SIX, divided, shows its subject scattering the (different) parties (in the state); which leads to great good fortune. From the dispersion (he collects again good men standing out, a crowd) like a mound, which is what ordinary men would not have thought of.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
